This is a basic 2 bombsite layout that's been painted in pretty and nice. In my opinion it looks like some sort of playground, but really if I had done it with proper textures it would look like some sort of processing facility or old fashioned mill. 
The layout is fair and fun, allowing the player to quickly change their route and situation. The only real dead end is the sniper tower. The area beyond the walls is out of play. The water wheels are rotating and deliver 1dmg per frame if blocked, however they are almost entirely player clipped.

[LL] Lord Azael for support/ideas/testing/uploading
[LL] Sibby for feedback/ideas

gg_dev_revolution: sketched this out on graph paper and i believe it turned out great. 
A large central building takes the spotlight here. Spawns are opposite, different ways of approaching the enemy. Several smaller building surround it. You must jump roof to roof to reach the top. The two buildings by the spawn have a camping spot. I decided to put some detail into this map with a border at the bottom of all the buildings and  a noticeable pipe running the outside of the buildings.

This is my first ever COMPLETED map.

I make maps a LOT but I never really complete them OR upload them. So after I talked with Shirk from FPSBanana about mapping, I decided to give it a good shot. 

So, this is a Gungame map, it uses the default DEV textures from VALVe, a few custom DEV textures from Chris528, and a custom skybox from GFLOW. Links available below.

=============FEATURES==============
 
*2 open towers on opposite sides of the map, entrances blocked by UNbreakable glass walls. (NOTE: the towers are tall and hollow but you cant reach the top and theres no platforms or multiple stories inside because in a gungame map that wouldnt make much sense :| )

*2 stories, the main level then a lower level with edges protected by player_clip so you can stare off the edge at the bottom of the skybox

*Half circle hiding spots

*Spawnpoints so that you can add buyzones or whatever you want, to the raw file and play whatever you want.

*Lighting that suits the skybox

*Custom FPSBanana logo clearly visible on the front of one of the towers (NOTE: The FPSBanana logo will be added to FPSBanana so you can position it in your maps :D But if you use it, could you please give me credit? Because it was a bit of work creating it :D

===============LINKS================

Gg_devdropdown
===========
The main point of this map was to create a very fast paced gun game.
Without the lag, maximizing fps and not destroying the fun of the game.
===========
Features a wall that separates the map forcing players to drop down to confront the opposing team. Stairs allow access from below, while 2 super-boosters allow you to fly across the map to immediately access the enemies spawn, at the risk of being killed by a spinning hoop.
===========
